This code defines a function `clean_column` that takes a string `col` as input. It applies three transformations to `col`: it converts it to lowercase, removes leading or trailing whitespaces, and replaces any spaces or hyphens with underscores. The function then returns the cleaned string. The last line is a test to ensure that the function is working correctly.
